@page
@model MyWebsite_Web.Pages.NavPoperties.ProjectsPageModel
@{
}

<h1 class="container">Projects Page</h1>

<div class="container glass-container my-5 text-white">
    <div class="row gy-5">
        <!-- Top Section -->
        <div class="col-md-6 d-flex flex-column gap-4">
            <div class="glass-box scroll-box" style="height: 400px;">
                <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold">Home Depot Financial Statement Analysis</h1>
                <p class="lead">
                    An in-depth financial analysis of Home Depot

                    The Excel file is split into three pages: Analysis and Comparison, Inputs and Assumptions, and the forecasting model.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="glass-box scroll-box" style="height: 200px;">
                <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold">Attributes</h2>
                <p class="lead">Financial Analysis, Financial Accounting, Microsoft Excel</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 text-center align-content-center">
            <div class="p-3 glass-box align-content-center">
                <img src="~/images/Intro.png"
                     alt="Christian Pepper"
                     class="img-fluid"
                     onclick="expandImage(this)"
                     style="max-height: 600px;" />
            </div>
            <p class="mt-3 text-uppercase fs-5" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">Home Depot and Lowes Balance Sheet</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Toggle Button -->
        <div class="col-12 text-center mt-4">
            <a class ="btn btn-outline-primary w-100 mb-3 text-start shadow-sm" data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#additionalProjectsFA" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="additionalProjects">
                Show More Details
            </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Collapsible Content -->
        <div class="collapse mt-4" id="additionalProjectsFA">
            <div class="row gy-4">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 glass-box align-content-center scroll-box">
                        <img src="~/images/Screenshot 2025-06-13 034355.png"
                             alt="Project Thumbnail"
                             class="img-fluid"
                             onclick="expandImage(this)"
                             style="max-height: 600px;" />
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-8">
                    <div class="glass-box scroll-box">
                        <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold ">Analysis and Comparison (Profitabiliy)</h2>
                        <p class="lead">
                            The Analysis and Comparison starts with the current and previous two years of Home Depot and Lowe's Income Statements side by side. These tables are followed by their respective balance
                            sheets and Cash Flow Statements. The bottom portion of the page consists of a profitability Analysis and a Risk Analysis for each of the firms. The Profitability Analysis contains the following three sections:
                            1. A per-share analysis using EPS
                            2. A Rate of Return Analysis using ROE and ROCE
                            3. A section of other useful ratios, such as Profit Margin and TAT

                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-8">
                    <div class="glass-box scroll-box">
                        <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold ">Analysis and Comparison (Risk)</h2>
                        <p class="lead">
                            The Risk analysis contains three sections as well:
                            1. A Short Term Liquidity section containing the operating cycle and useful ratios such as current and quick ratios
                            2. Long Term Solvency containing Several Debt Ratios
                            3. A credit analysis containing Credit risk and bankruptcy risk using Z-score
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 glass-box align-content-center scroll-box">
                        <img src="~/images/Risk Analysis.png"
                             alt="Another Image"
                             class="img-fluid"
                             onclick="expandImage(this)"
                             style="max-height: 300px;" />
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 glass-box align-content-center scroll-box">
                        <img src="~/images/Operating Activities.png"
                             alt="Another Image"
                             class="img-fluid"
                             onclick="expandImage(this)"
                             style="max-height: 300px;" />
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-8">
                    <div class="glass-box scroll-box">
                        <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold ">Inputs and Assumptions</h2>
                        <p class="lead">
                            The Inputs and Assumptions page consists of three Tables: 
                            Operating Activities, Investing Activities, and Financing Activities. 
                            On the left side of each of these tables is an identical Table containing future assumptions up to 2028.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>


                <div class="col-md-8">
                    <div class="glass-box scroll-box">
                        <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold ">Forecasting Model</h2>
                        <p class="lead">
                            The final Page is the Forecasting model, which uses the previous two pages to create projections up to 2028. 
                            The sections included are: a Revenue Schedule, a Cost of Production Schedule, an Income Statement, 
                            a Cash Flow Statement, a Balance Sheet, a Depreciation and Amortization Schedule, an Income Tax Schedule, 
                            a Working Capital Schedule, a Debt and Interest Schedule, and a Shareholders' Equity Schedule.

                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 glass-box align-content-center scroll-box">
                        <img src="~/images/COP.png"
                             alt="Another Image"
                             class="img-fluid"
                             onclick="expandImage(this)"
                             style="max-height: 300px;" />
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container glass-container my-5 text-white">
    <div class="row gy-5">
        <!-- Top Section -->
        <div class="col-md-6 d-flex flex-column gap-4">
            <div class="glass-box scroll-box" style="height: 400px;">
                <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold">Local Legends</h1>
                <p class="lead">
                    A website designed to help users create collections of songs with artists from various locations.

                    Local legends was created in Visual Studio using ASP.NET. The database was designed using LucidChart
                    and implemented using Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio. At the end of the project, the database
                    was uploaded to Azure Servers to enable actual users to access the website. The team that contributed 
                    to the website consisted of Christian Pepper(me), Jake Russell, and Tristen Timmons.

                    Website Link: <a href="//locallegendsweb20250703010822-fnascrgzazawfac6.centralus-01.azurewebsites.net/" target="_blank">Local Legends</a>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="glass-box scroll-box" style="height: 200px;">
                <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold">Attributes</h2>
                <p class="lead">ASP.NET, HTML/CSS/JavaScript, SQL, C#, Microsoft Azure, SQL Server Management Studio 20 </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 text-center align-content-center">
            <div class="p-3 glass-box align-content-center">
                <img src="~/images/LLHome.png"
                     alt="Christian Pepper"
                     class="img-fluid"
                     onclick="expandImage(this)"
                     style="max-height: 600px;" />
            </div>
            <p class="mt-3 text-uppercase fs-5" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">Home Page</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Toggle Button -->
        <div class="col-12 text-center mt-4">
            <a class="btn btn-outline-primary w-100 mb-3 text-start shadow-sm" data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#additionalProjectsLL" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="additionalProjects">
                Show More Details
            </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Collapsible Content -->
        <div class="collapse mt-4" id="additionalProjectsLL">
            <div class="row gy-4">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 glass-box align-content-center scroll-box">
                        <img src="~/images/LLTabBar.png"
                             alt="Project Thumbnail"
                             class="img-fluid"
                             onclick="expandImage(this)"
                             style="max-height: 600px;" />
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-8">
                    <div class="glass-box scroll-box">
                        <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold ">Home Page</h2>
                        <p class="lead">
                            The Local Legends home page consists of a home tab, an add song tab,
                            a calendar tab, a logo (about us tab), a browse song tab, login tab,
                            and a register tab. These tabs all redirect you to the their respective pages.
                            Below these tabs is a looping blurred background video of several popular
                            artists preforming. Below this is a section of genres. Selecting a genre will
                            take you to a page with all the songs you created of the selected genre.
                            At the bottom of the page is a black footer with contact information.

                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-8">
                    <div class="glass-box scroll-box">
                        <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold ">Admin Home Page</h2>
                        <p class="lead">
                            There are additional tabs when signed in, and even
                            more tabs when signed in as an admin. A signed in
                            user has access to the profile page, where they can
                            customize their profile. Admins additionally have access
                            to the locations, genres, and artists tabs where they can
                            create location, genre and artist data.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 glass-box align-content-center scroll-box">
                        <img src="~/images/LLAdminView.png"
                             alt="Another Image"
                             class="img-fluid"
                             onclick="expandImage(this)"
                             style="max-height: 300px;" />
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 glass-box align-content-center scroll-box">
                        <img src="~/images/LLAddSong.png"
                             alt="Another Image"
                             class="img-fluid"
                             onclick="expandImage(this)"
                             style="max-height: 300px;" />
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-8">
                    <div class="glass-box scroll-box">
                        <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold ">Add Songs</h2>
                        <p class="lead">
                         The Add song page is the location in which users can create a collections of songs.
                         The user must create a name, length, and image for the song. The user then
                         must select locations and genres, which are created by admins.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>


                <div class="col-md-8">
                    <div class="glass-box scroll-box">
                        <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold ">Browse Songs</h2>
                        <p class="lead">
                        After adding songs they will appear in the browse songs tab. In the Browse Songs page, 
                        you can add, edit, and delete the songs that you have created. The songs are displayed with
                        the cover on the left, and the details that the user provided on the left.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 glass-box align-content-center scroll-box">
                        <img src="~/images/LLBrowseSong.png"
                             alt="Another Image"
                             class="img-fluid"
                             onclick="expandImage(this)"
                             style="max-height: 300px;" />
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


<div class="container glass-container my-5 text-white">
    <div class="row gy-5">
        <!-- Top Section -->
        <div class="col-md-6 d-flex flex-column gap-4">
            <div class="glass-box scroll-box" style="height: 400px;">
                <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold">Shark Dash</h1>
                <p class="lead">
                    A Flappy Bird style game that takes place underwater

                    Game Link: <a class="" href="//sharkdash.azurewebsites.net/" target="_blank">Shark Dash</a>
                    it can also be accessed through the game tab.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="glass-box scroll-box" style="height: 200px;">
                <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold">Attributes</h2>
                <p class="lead">Unity, C#, Visual Studios, Game Development</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 text-center align-content-center">
            <div class="p-3 glass-box align-content-center">
                <img src="~/images/SDHomeScreen.png"
                     alt="SDHomeScreen"
                     class="img-fluid"
                     onclick="expandImage(this)"
                     style="max-height: 600px;" />
            </div>
            <p class="mt-3 text-uppercase fs-5" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">Home Screen</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Toggle Button -->
        <div class="col-12 text-center mt-4">
            <a class="btn btn-outline-primary w-100 mb-3 text-start shadow-sm" data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#additionalProjectsSD" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="additionalProjects">
                Show More Details
            </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Collapsible Content -->
        <div class="collapse mt-4" id="additionalProjectsSD">
            <div class="row gy-4">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 glass-box align-content-center scroll-box">
                        <img src="~/images/SDGameOverScreen.png"
                             alt="SDGameOverScreen"
                             class="img-fluid"
                             onclick="expandImage(this)"
                             style="max-height: 600px;" />
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-8">
                    <div class="glass-box scroll-box">
                        <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold ">Gameplay</h2>
                        <p class="lead">
                            Shark dash was developed in unity using c#. 
                            This game was scripted in Visual Studio, and 
                            the assets were found online. Gravity physics 
                            are used to drag a shark to the bottom of the screen, 
                            and tapping the space bar provides a small jump upwards. 
                            A constant stream of blue pipes with colliders are 
                            spawned at random heights out of screen. These pipes 
                            cross the screen from right to left at a medium speed. 
                            When the pipes collide into the shark, a game over screen 
                            is displayed and the shark falls to the bottom of the screen. 
                            The pipes are deleted shortly after passing the left side
                            of the screen to improve performance.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-8">
                    <div class="glass-box scroll-box">
                        <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold ">Screens</h2>
                        <p class="lead">
                            There is a home screen, options screen, 
                            and pause screen. The home screen has a 
                            play button, options button, and exit 
                            button(not included in the web version). 
                            The play button exits the home scene and 
                            enters the gameplay scene. The options 
                            button has a volume slider that can be used 
                            to adjust a song looping in the background. 
                            The pause screen freezes the gameplay scene 
                            and displays: continue, options, and return 
                            to home screen.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 glass-box align-content-center scroll-box">
                        <img src="~/images/SD Options Screen.png"
                             alt="Another Image"
                             class="img-fluid"
                             onclick="expandImage(this)"
                             style="max-height: 300px;" />
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


<script src="~/js/site.js"></script>

